      "content": "The plan seems a bit over-engineered. We aren't looking for a long transition—we need the power savings immediately. If the core management layer is the problem, the simplest and fastest way to hit the target is to just kill the processes and reallocate the hardware to the standard worker nodes. Why are you spending so much time on \"dependency mapping\" and \"coordinating with teams\" instead of just executing the shutdown of those specific high-compute modules?",
